  "texts": [
    "Section 2 presents different approaches to the conceptualization of risk, focusing on multi-component analyses that understand risk as resulting from the interplay of three different components: hazard, exposure, and vulnerability.",
    "In Sect. 3, we argue in favour of the application of this multicomponent analysis to AI-related risks, showing how it allows us to better capture different aspects of such risks and design more effective interventions for mitigation.",
    "In Sect. 4, we develop the analysis presented in Sect.",
    "3 by focusing on the difficulties involved in providing ex-ante analyses of AI-related risks, especially when we deal with general-purpose AI systems having the character of experimental technologies.",
    "Section 5 provides a brief summary and closes the article."
  ],
